# Workflow Decisions

This file is the **record** of every workflow decision this project has made — a
single human-readable index of the tunable settings you chose and where each value lives.
(Not to be confused with `.claude/memory/decisions.md`, which records *architecture*
decisions about the code itself.)

> **How this works.** For speed, each setting's *live* value is written directly
> into the skill that uses it — **skills do not read this file at runtime.** This
> file mirrors those values and records the exact location of each one. The two are
> kept in sync by the `/workflow-decisions` skill:
>
> - **To change a setting:** run `/workflow-decisions` (optionally naming the setting,
>   e.g. `/workflow-decisions refine sizing`). It edits the live value in the skill(s)
>   *and* updates the matching entry here, in one commit — so they never drift.
> - **To change it by hand:** edit the skill at the listed **Live in** location,
>   then update the **Current** value in the matching entry here to match.
>
> Each entry lists **Live in** (the file that actually drives behavior), the
> **Current** value, and the allowed **Options**.

