## Refinement

### Sizing defaults
How `/refine` scales autonomy, approval, and the refinement tier (model+effort for planning agents and per-ticket review) by assessed ticket size.
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/refine/SKILL.md` — §0.2 tier table
- **Current:**

  | Tier | Autonomy | Approval | Rounds | Refinement tier |
  |------|----------|----------|--------|-----------------|
  | trivial | fully-autonomous — no questions | auto-accept | fast-track (1 TP pass) | sonnet-high |
  | small | fully-autonomous — no questions | auto-accept | 1 | opus-high |
  | medium | key-questions-only — 1–3 questions | auto-accept | 1 | opus-high |
  | large | many-questions — interview mode | manual-approval | 3 | best-high |

- **Options:** autonomy ∈ {fully-autonomous, key-questions-only, many-questions} · approval ∈ {auto-accept, manual-approval} · rounds ∈ non-negative integer · tier ∈ {sonnet-medium, sonnet-high, opus-medium, opus-high, best-medium, best-high}
- **Note:** the tier is assessed automatically and applied without asking; you are only consulted on sizing if you explicitly ask to be. In unsupervised mode no questions are asked at any tier and specs are self-approved.

