## Model & Effort Routing

### Agent tier pins
Which model/effort each subagent is pinned to (mechanical → haiku/medium; writers → sonnet/medium; product-owner → sonnet/high; RE/tech-planner → effort high, model per ticket; reviewers → per review tier).
- **Live in:** each agent file's `model:`/`effort:` frontmatter under `.claude/agents/`
- **Current:** plugin defaults, exactly as listed in the description above
- **Options:** model ∈ {haiku, sonnet, opus, fable, inherit} · effort ∈ {medium, high} per agent (low/xhigh deliberately unused here)

### Top-tier mapping
What the `best` tier (route-best-* skills, /consult) resolves to.
- **Live in:** `.claude/skills/route-best-medium/SKILL.md` + `.claude/skills/route-best-high/SKILL.md` + `.claude/skills/consult/SKILL.md` frontmatter
- **Current:** `fable` — best-medium = `model: best, effort: medium`; best-high = `model: best, effort: high` (`best` = Fable if available, else latest Opus)
- **Options:** `fable` (as above) · `opus-compensated` — best-medium = `model: opus, effort: high`; best-high = `model: opus, effort: xhigh`. Switch when Fable access has ended.

### Adaptive routing
Whether Claude may deviate from planned tiers during execution (see the Adaptive Routing Policy in the project CLAUDE.md).
- **Live in:** root `CLAUDE.md` — "Adaptive Routing Policy" + `.claude/skills/implement/SKILL.md` — "Adaptive routing during implementation"
- **Current:** `on` — escalate at medium threshold (consult first), de-escalate at high threshold, gates never adaptive
- **Options:** `on` · `escalate-only` · `off` (spec routing always applied verbatim)
